01:37.848 --> 01:40.016
Have a seat, Nash.

01:41.476 --> 01:43.352
Let's get down to business.

01:43.353 --> 01:46.939
I'd like to introduce
you to Mohamed Asan,

01:46.940 --> 01:50.144
or T3, as the boys in DC call him.

01:52.362 --> 01:54.280
Number three on the
Al-Qaeda most-wanted list.

01:54.281 --> 01:57.575
Very well-trained,
very difficult to track.

01:57.576 --> 02:00.161
CIA's been following
this guy for two years.

02:00.162 --> 02:01.871
Every time they think
they have him...

02:01.872 --> 02:04.081
poof, he just disappears.

02:04.082 --> 02:06.626
The man's a fucking ghost.

02:06.627 --> 02:10.880
He travels in small groups, often with
women and children to avoid air strikes.

02:10.881 --> 02:14.008
We've currently got intel that
he's leading a small force

02:14.009 --> 02:17.637
operating out of the lower
quadrant of Sector 4.

02:17.638 --> 02:19.681
Sector 4, sir?

02:24.227 --> 02:26.020
Why?

02:26.021 --> 02:27.438
That a problem?

02:27.439 --> 02:30.149
It's a mess down there, sir.
It's the red zone.

02:30.150 --> 02:33.069
That's why they called us.

02:33.070 --> 02:34.070
When do we leave?

02:34.071 --> 02:38.199
ASAP. Get your team together.

02:38.200 --> 02:39.902
Copy that.

03:33.046 --> 03:35.214
Commander Reynolds on deck.

03:46.476 --> 03:49.520
Confirming two souls on
board, dark-colored pickup,

03:49.521 --> 03:51.355
traveling west-bound
towards village.

03:51.356 --> 03:53.729
Keep your eyes on the target.

04:03.827 --> 04:07.163
Do we have confirmation
Tango 3 is in the vehicle?

04:07.164 --> 04:09.366
It's now confirmed
Tango 3 is on board.

04:23.346 --> 04:25.890
We have visual on the target.

04:25.891 --> 04:28.844
- Scramble the jets.
- Sir.

04:33.482 --> 04:36.358
Countdown 55, space checker
at transponder setting

04:36.359 --> 04:39.403
03 Alpha, 4750.

04:54.586 --> 04:57.546
All right, target one

04:57.547 --> 05:00.257
by the entrance.

05:00.258 --> 05:02.718
- Three plus...
- I'm picking up a signal.

05:02.719 --> 05:05.095
It looks like we've got some
friendlies in Sector 4.

05:05.096 --> 05:07.640
Sector 4? We don't have
anybody in Sector 4.

05:07.641 --> 05:10.060
We have guys over in Sector 5.
4 should be clear.

05:12.395 --> 05:14.973
All right, what do you have for me?

05:16.650 --> 05:18.108
Target one,

05:18.109 --> 05:20.903
by the entrance.

05:20.904 --> 05:23.531
Three plus down.

05:23.532 --> 05:25.530
Target one.

05:27.118 --> 05:28.661
Three plus down.

05:28.662 --> 05:31.081
I am showing something
from that area, sir.

05:36.670 --> 05:40.172
Those are our GPS signals.

05:40.173 --> 05:42.508
A team of four?

05:42.509 --> 05:45.758
- All right, let me contact I-Corps.
- Sir.

05:49.641 --> 05:54.436
All right then. Wind,
three knots east-west.

05:54.437 --> 05:56.772
The wind...

05:56.773 --> 05:59.101
three knots east-west.

06:04.364 --> 06:06.441
There's no way we could be
positive it's our guys.

06:08.076 --> 06:10.452
All right, and target two...

06:10.453 --> 06:15.284
four feet left to target one.

06:16.293 --> 06:18.043
Target two acquired.

06:18.044 --> 06:20.337
We have degree coordinates
on that target.

06:20.338 --> 06:23.173
Confirming the grid, 68-niner 517.

06:23.174 --> 06:25.634
This could be Al-Qaeda
trying to throw us off.

06:25.635 --> 06:28.634
Understood, sir.
Proceeding with the strike.

06:35.437 --> 06:38.230
All right, boss,
ready for your call.

06:38.231 --> 06:39.603
Fire.

06:57.667 --> 07:00.211
We've got heavy contact!

07:11.973 --> 07:13.974
Shit!

07:13.975 --> 07:15.677
Ahh!

07:19.356 --> 07:21.482
Oh shit! What was that?!

07:21.483 --> 07:22.684
Air strike!

07:27.614 --> 07:29.031
What the fuck was that?

07:29.032 --> 07:31.200
Where the hell did all
these people come from?

07:34.204 --> 07:36.873
- I'm on red! Cover me, Scott!
- I got it, I got it!

07:40.669 --> 07:42.711
On the ground! I'm green. Clear!

07:42.712 --> 07:44.755
- Ah!
- Copy that!

07:44.756 --> 07:48.051
- Cover me!
- Watch out!

07:49.803 --> 07:51.303
Ah!

07:51.304 --> 07:53.757
- Move into the cave!
- Go! Moving!

08:00.313 --> 08:01.935
Go!

08:04.192 --> 08:06.568
Go, let's get to the cave!

08:06.569 --> 08:08.771
Roger that! Moving.

08:12.200 --> 08:13.283
Let's go.

08:13.284 --> 08:16.328
- Shit! Ahhh!
- Shit.

08:16.329 --> 08:19.623
- We've got one man down!
- Nash, I'm hit.

08:19.624 --> 08:21.250
- Nash, Nash...
- I got you, I got you.

08:21.251 --> 08:24.204
Okay! Ahh!

08:27.590 --> 08:29.842
Oh, shit!

08:29.843 --> 08:31.590
Son of a...

08:32.511 --> 08:34.596
- Put pressure.
- Shit!

08:34.597 --> 08:37.140
I got you.

08:38.308 --> 08:41.638
- Put pressure on that!
- Yeah, I can make it. Yeah.

08:43.940 --> 08:48.152
We got heavy contact! Green 745.

08:48.153 --> 08:50.902
- All right, let's go! Move move move!
- My leg!

09:02.292 --> 09:03.625
Oh, Nash!

09:03.626 --> 09:05.335
What the fuck was that?

09:05.336 --> 09:06.962
Fuck Al-Qaeda.

09:06.963 --> 09:08.631
Guys, what's your status?

09:10.467 --> 09:12.089
What's your status?

09:12.927 --> 09:15.129
I got contact left!

09:15.972 --> 09:17.799
Contact right, contact right!

09:19.100 --> 09:21.268
Allahu akbar!

09:24.230 --> 09:26.482
They're everywhere!

09:26.483 --> 09:28.481
Nash, what's your location?

09:37.035 --> 09:39.579
Steve, what's your location?

09:40.663 --> 09:42.991
What's your location?

09:54.511 --> 09:56.338
Hold on, I'm coming for you.

10:42.517 --> 10:46.311
Pizza! Pizza! Pizza!

10:46.312 --> 10:48.480
No running in the house.

10:54.529 --> 10:56.780
I like what you did with the house.

10:56.781 --> 10:58.532
Thanks! I know I shouldn't

10:58.533 --> 11:00.367
spend the money, but I get lonely.

11:00.368 --> 11:02.369
He's gone for months at a time.

11:02.370 --> 11:04.955
I have to find some way to
keep myself from going crazy.

11:04.956 --> 11:07.249
Think you're going crazy?

11:07.250 --> 11:10.377
It's been over three
months since Scott left.

11:10.378 --> 11:13.463
That's how long it's
been since I've had sex.

11:13.464 --> 11:16.466
Try living in the same house
as your ex-husband and his son

11:16.467 --> 11:19.469
- and see how great your sex life is.
- Oh, no way.

11:19.470 --> 11:23.182
I don't know. After
this mission's over,

11:23.183 --> 11:25.559
I only want three things...

11:25.560 --> 11:29.479
peace, love...

11:29.480 --> 11:31.023
and sex.

11:31.024 --> 11:34.234
Yeah, I want more sex.

11:34.235 --> 11:36.945
- Pizza pizza!
- This is so good, guys.

11:36.946 --> 11:39.069
Thanks, Mom!

11:45.371 --> 11:47.164
It's 20 individuals.

11:47.165 --> 11:49.959
Roger tally. Right door.

12:31.376 --> 12:33.624
American.

12:49.310 --> 12:51.853
clear, anytime, come
in on that road.

12:51.854 --> 12:54.056
I got individuals everywhere.

15:00.400 --> 15:02.526
Alpha 4, we've got confirmation

15:02.527 --> 15:05.105
of friendly in the area, running
north away from the village.

16:32.283 --> 16:34.235
I love you, Dad.

16:40.791 --> 16:43.585
Your son needs you.

16:53.930 --> 16:55.847
Keep eyes on target.

16:55.848 --> 16:59.100
Roger. What's your location.

16:59.101 --> 17:00.977
Charlie 5, Charlie 6 has got bingo.

17:00.978 --> 17:04.814
Charlie 1 through
6, return to base.

17:04.815 --> 17:07.983
7-India-53, one length to location.

17:07.984 --> 17:10.983
You have the call.
They're on their way, sir.

17:55.741 --> 17:57.739
All right, let's pump him up.

18:17.930 --> 18:20.307
I have an update on
Operation Mikaela, sir.

18:20.308 --> 18:22.017
- Let's have it!
- The enemy focused

18:22.018 --> 18:24.227
most of their strength on
this area during the attack.

18:24.228 --> 18:26.021
Much higher numbers
than we anticipated.

18:26.022 --> 18:27.439
Okay, what about the target?

18:27.440 --> 18:29.566
Unfortunately, the
target escaped, sir.

18:29.567 --> 18:31.359
What's the status
of the contractors?

18:31.360 --> 18:33.486
We received a friendly
GPS signal in the area.

18:33.487 --> 18:35.488
We had no way of knowing
it was the contractors,

18:35.489 --> 18:38.575
so we proceeded with the air strike.
We lost all of them but one.

18:38.576 --> 18:41.536
- What the fuck just happened?!
- I just heard it myself.

18:41.537 --> 18:43.121
I don't know all the details yet.

18:43.122 --> 18:45.332
The details are simple...
you're in charge

18:45.333 --> 18:46.916
of the private fucking contractors,

18:46.917 --> 18:48.877
and they got in the
middle of a fire zone

18:48.878 --> 18:50.462
when we launched an air strike!

18:50.463 --> 18:52.172
We may have just
killed our own men.

18:52.173 --> 18:54.257
It'll be taken care of.

18:54.258 --> 18:56.085
Son of a bitch.

19:45.601 --> 19:47.519
I'm hit!

19:47.520 --> 19:49.518
Nash, I'm hit!

20:24.515 --> 20:26.808
A knock would be more appropriate,

20:26.809 --> 20:29.307
if you don't mind.

20:34.567 --> 20:36.818
Roger that.

20:36.819 --> 20:38.069
Where's Max?

20:38.070 --> 20:39.529
He's out back playing.

20:39.530 --> 20:42.657
You know, he asks about you a lot.

20:42.658 --> 20:46.035
I'm running out of excuses.

20:46.036 --> 20:50.081
When are you going to stop
blaming yourself for the past

20:50.082 --> 20:53.081
and start being a better
father to your son?

20:56.172 --> 20:59.251
It's not too late
for that, you know?

21:01.552 --> 21:03.504
I'm working on it, okay?

21:15.024 --> 21:16.350
Dad!

21:26.827 --> 21:28.495
- Dad?
- Buddy?

21:28.496 --> 21:31.498
Do you know that the Grand
Canyon's over 6,000 feet deep,

21:31.499 --> 21:33.541
and over 20 football fields

21:33.542 --> 21:36.002
and 277 miles long?

21:36.003 --> 21:37.754
No, I didn't know that.

21:37.755 --> 21:39.673
- You didn't?
- No.

21:41.425 --> 21:44.511
But you said we can go to
the Grand Canyon one day.

21:44.512 --> 21:46.262
You know what?

21:46.263 --> 21:49.307
I know I promised you we'd
go to the Grand Canyon.

21:49.308 --> 21:52.560
You know? But I'm telling you...

21:52.561 --> 21:54.938
I promise, okay?

21:54.939 --> 21:56.561
Okay.

21:59.401 --> 22:02.650
Oh, I love you, buddy. Come here.

22:08.619 --> 22:10.571
I love you, Dad.

26:21.288 --> 26:22.580
You have a phone call, boss.

26:22.581 --> 26:24.249
Thank you, Jacob.

26:25.167 --> 26:26.751
Nash?

26:26.752 --> 26:29.671
Sir, I just received an
email, I don't know from who.

26:31.423 --> 26:32.840
It's a video, sir.

26:34.384 --> 26:35.836
Excuse me?

26:37.513 --> 26:39.556
They're alive, sir.

26:40.390 --> 26:42.600
I see.

26:42.601 --> 26:45.520
And what exactly would you
like us to do about it?

26:45.521 --> 26:48.356
We need to get them out, sir.
We don't have much time.

26:48.357 --> 26:49.857
Mikaela was classified.

26:49.858 --> 26:51.692
There's no way we can go back now.

26:51.693 --> 26:53.861
Sir, you're telling me you
know my men are alive

26:53.862 --> 26:57.073
and you're not going to do
anything about it, right?

26:57.074 --> 27:00.201
You know what you're getting into
every time you accept a mission.

27:00.202 --> 27:01.911
That's the life you chose.

27:01.912 --> 27:04.455
That's why you're making
the big bucks, pal.

27:04.456 --> 27:08.960
No one gets left behind, sir.

27:08.961 --> 27:11.212
You're not soldiers,
you're mercenaries.

27:11.213 --> 27:13.131
No one cares about a
team of hired guns

27:13.132 --> 27:15.550
getting stuck behind enemy lines.

27:15.551 --> 27:17.635
You know what?

27:17.636 --> 27:19.887
The more I think back
to that mission...

27:19.888 --> 27:22.056
the air strikes,

27:22.057 --> 27:25.476
the men that were not
supposed to be there...

27:25.477 --> 27:29.230
the more I think you're
covering up something, sir.

27:29.231 --> 27:31.809
I'm sorry, Nash. There's
nothing I can do.

27:39.908 --> 27:41.655
He's going back.

27:42.744 --> 27:44.036
This is Aisha Nasser,

27:44.037 --> 27:47.415
reporting live from the
Afghanistan/Pakistan border,

27:47.416 --> 27:50.084
a region now referred
to as Sector 4.

27:50.085 --> 27:52.837
It is believed that many of
the top Al-Qaeda leaders

27:52.838 --> 27:54.839
are operating out of this area.

27:54.840 --> 27:58.009
Recently, the government deemed
Sector 4 to be a red zone...

27:58.010 --> 28:02.180
an area too unsafe to orchestrate
ground assaults by US troops,

28:02.181 --> 28:04.432
making many of the
top Al-Qaeda leaders

28:04.433 --> 28:07.185
seemingly untouchable
by the US troops.

28:07.186 --> 28:11.562
This is Aisha Nasser reporting
live from Sector 4. Back to you.

29:59.923 --> 30:01.716
Come on!

30:02.926 --> 30:04.252
Come on!

30:07.973 --> 30:09.891
Come on!

30:11.977 --> 30:13.811
Do it!

30:13.812 --> 30:16.188
Do it, you fucking pig!

30:16.189 --> 30:18.187
Do it!

30:21.903 --> 30:24.363
Chickenshit! Fuck!

30:24.364 --> 30:27.575
You don't have the guts! Come on!

30:27.576 --> 30:30.746
Come on! Gaaaah!

30:50.307 --> 30:53.101
What the fuck are you looking at?

30:56.772 --> 30:57.813
Are you all right?

30:57.814 --> 30:59.565
- Buddy.
- Come on.

30:59.566 --> 31:01.268
You doin' all right?

31:09.034 --> 31:11.328
I can't take this anymore.

31:12.788 --> 31:14.740
We're getting out of here.

31:16.291 --> 31:18.493
We're not going to get out of here.

31:19.628 --> 31:20.961
Yeah.

31:20.962 --> 31:23.210
We're gonna wait.

31:24.674 --> 31:27.134
I'm done waiting.

31:27.135 --> 31:28.803
Nash will be here.

31:28.804 --> 31:30.506
You'll see.

31:39.815 --> 31:41.767
You know, in the war days...

31:43.402 --> 31:45.820
I was in the same situation.

31:45.821 --> 31:48.155
I lost some...

31:48.156 --> 31:50.324
I lost some of my nearest friends.

31:50.325 --> 31:53.495
They were left behind,
but I was told to stand down.

31:55.372 --> 31:57.498
I did.

31:57.499 --> 32:00.418
Not a day goes by I don't
think about those faces

32:00.419 --> 32:03.168
or see them.

32:04.423 --> 32:06.340
If you're going to go
to one of the craziest

32:06.341 --> 32:09.552
parts of the world...
the most dangerous...

32:09.553 --> 32:12.138
you're going to have
to fight the people,

32:12.139 --> 32:14.056
the elements, the weather,

32:14.057 --> 32:15.975
the desert,

32:15.976 --> 32:18.269
the snow, skydive...

32:18.270 --> 32:19.938
by yourself.

32:23.316 --> 32:26.110
You need to get mentally strong

32:26.111 --> 32:28.734
so you can survive
and see your kid.

32:30.866 --> 32:33.410
Make sure you say
good night to him.

32:43.670 --> 32:45.838
Let's do it.

32:55.265 --> 32:57.349
We gotta get the fuck out of here.

32:57.350 --> 32:59.678
How do you suppose we're gonna
get the fuck out of here?

33:01.730 --> 33:05.566
We've been a team for
how long? How long?

33:05.567 --> 33:07.776
Our wives hang out together...

33:07.777 --> 33:09.737
we're a team.

33:09.738 --> 33:12.072
Yeah, he's not going to
leave anybody behind.

33:12.073 --> 33:15.117
I feel pretty fucking abandoned.

33:15.118 --> 33:18.746
Been, what? 70-some
fuckin' days in here?

33:18.747 --> 33:21.081
Ain't no one coming for us.

33:21.082 --> 33:23.584
He's gonna come for us.

33:23.585 --> 33:25.336
He's gonna be here.

33:25.337 --> 33:27.463
Just trust him.

33:27.464 --> 33:30.258
Trust him... he'll be here.

33:36.431 --> 33:38.641
Dude, that's gonna get you killed.

33:38.642 --> 33:40.476
We're gonna get killed anyway.

33:40.477 --> 33:44.313
At least this is
going to be my way.

33:44.314 --> 33:46.690
My kids are not going
to watch their dad

33:46.691 --> 33:48.776
have his head cut off

33:48.777 --> 33:51.275
and watch it on TV.

33:56.952 --> 33:59.036
Nash will be here.

33:59.037 --> 34:01.872
He'll be here. You'll see.

34:01.873 --> 34:05.334
He'll be here.

34:05.335 --> 34:08.629
You just gotta stand down

34:08.630 --> 34:10.831
and be a little stronger.

34:38.827 --> 34:41.576
He'll be back.

34:56.344 --> 34:58.512
You're going back, aren't you?

35:00.682 --> 35:02.008
Yep.

35:08.690 --> 35:11.525
You know,

35:11.526 --> 35:14.855
I actually thought this time
was going to be different.

35:16.823 --> 35:18.741
For the first time I believed

35:18.742 --> 35:21.368
that you were going
to change things

35:21.369 --> 35:24.371
and be a better father to Max.

35:24.372 --> 35:26.874
I can't leave them behind.

35:26.875 --> 35:29.543
What about Max?

35:29.544 --> 35:32.042
You're leaving him behind.

35:36.051 --> 35:38.344
All this week he's been
talking about the trip

35:38.345 --> 35:41.219
that you two were supposed
to take to the Grand Canyon.

35:43.308 --> 35:46.432
That should be your priority.

35:48.730 --> 35:51.774
Jesus, Nash.

35:53.568 --> 35:57.529
I know you could care less
what happened between us.

35:57.530 --> 36:00.233
Lord knows I'm over it.

36:02.118 --> 36:05.288
I really love those guys too.

36:06.539 --> 36:08.957
But a real man,

36:08.958 --> 36:13.128
a good father, knows
when to turn his back

36:13.129 --> 36:16.256
and let somebody else
take care of the problem.

36:16.257 --> 36:18.092
There is nobody else.

36:18.093 --> 36:19.760
You're just trying to play hero

36:19.761 --> 36:21.762
so you can feel better
about yourself.

36:21.763 --> 36:23.555
Meanwhile I'm taking care of Max,

36:23.556 --> 36:26.009
not knowing if you're coming back.

36:28.269 --> 36:31.268
Which is why I divorced you.

36:32.982 --> 36:35.275
We live in the same house,

36:35.276 --> 36:38.529
and I am okay with that,

36:38.530 --> 36:41.654
but don't go out and
get yourself killed.

