01:23:22.748 --> 01:23:24.749
It is good to see you, Nash.

01:23:24.750 --> 01:23:26.959
Is it?

01:23:26.960 --> 01:23:29.754
So how are the men?

01:23:29.755 --> 01:23:32.882
I got Steven out. Brad
and Scott are dead,

01:23:32.883 --> 01:23:35.468
but I'm sure you already
know that, don't you, sir?

01:23:35.469 --> 01:23:37.386
I'm sorry about that, Nash.
Really, I am.

01:23:37.387 --> 01:23:41.057
But like I said, that's why you
guys make the big bucks, right?

01:23:41.058 --> 01:23:43.768
You risk it all.

01:23:43.769 --> 01:23:46.771
You are the one who
sent me that video.

01:23:46.772 --> 01:23:49.106
You knew bin Laden's location,

01:23:49.107 --> 01:23:51.567
knowing that I would
go back in Sector 4,

01:23:51.568 --> 01:23:53.694
create enough chaos

01:23:53.695 --> 01:23:56.906
so it would open the window for the
military to move in on bin Laden.

01:23:56.907 --> 01:23:58.157
Am I correct, sir?

01:23:58.158 --> 01:24:00.910
With less forces
protecting bin Laden,

01:24:00.911 --> 01:24:02.954
the better chance we
had to take him out

01:24:02.955 --> 01:24:06.707
- with safety to our men.
- What about my men?

01:24:06.708 --> 01:24:10.044
You used them as bait.

01:24:10.045 --> 01:24:13.047
You sent us on a
suicide mission, sir.

01:24:13.048 --> 01:24:16.548
The only problem is
I am still alive.

01:24:20.389 --> 01:24:23.057
Men like us don't operate
on nobility and honor,

01:24:23.058 --> 01:24:26.102
so don't... so don't bullshit
with some hero act.

01:24:26.103 --> 01:24:28.479
War has become a very
lucrative business

01:24:28.480 --> 01:24:30.690
and made me a very rich man.

01:24:30.691 --> 01:24:33.064
So how much will it take?

01:24:34.778 --> 01:24:36.901
Hmph!

01:24:38.323 --> 01:24:40.157
Nothing is going to change anyway.

01:24:40.158 --> 01:24:43.327
So I want a proper military
service for my two men.

01:24:43.328 --> 01:24:44.704
That's number one.

01:24:44.705 --> 01:24:47.875
Number two, I want a big
check and I mean a big one.

01:24:49.209 --> 01:24:53.835
And number three,
I want out for good, sir.

01:24:59.011 --> 01:25:00.511
I'll miss you.

01:25:00.512 --> 01:25:02.931
Okay, here we go.

01:25:14.943 --> 01:25:18.904
That'll buy your kid a
nice shiny new bike.

01:25:18.905 --> 01:25:21.407
Hmm. It's not only for me, sir.

01:25:21.408 --> 01:25:24.368
I'm sorry to hear that, Nash.

01:25:24.369 --> 01:25:28.372
I had a job lined up you'd
be the perfect man for.

01:25:28.373 --> 01:25:30.750
I'm sure you did.

01:25:30.751 --> 01:25:34.546
I already got a job, sir.
Thank you.

01:25:36.298 --> 01:25:39.047
Damn, I thought he was dead.

01:26:35.273 --> 01:26:37.692
No one left behind.

01:26:37.693 --> 01:26:40.111
We lived and died by those words.

01:26:40.112 --> 01:26:43.280
Turns out, maybe we did not
understand what that meant,

01:26:43.281 --> 01:26:46.200
who was actually being left behind.

01:26:48.078 --> 01:26:51.622
Many soldiers lose their
lives to save others.

01:26:51.623 --> 01:26:54.417
Not everyone understands
why they do it,

01:26:54.418 --> 01:26:58.045
sometimes not even
their own family,

01:26:58.046 --> 01:27:00.715
because they are the
ones left behind,

01:27:00.716 --> 01:27:03.886
the ones that have to deal
with the loss and the pain.

01:27:05.470 --> 01:27:09.765
But now I'm making the same
promise to you and Max...

01:27:09.766 --> 01:27:12.594
to never leave you behind again.

